This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama in 2013. The memorandum designates officers of the Office of the Director of National Intelligence to act as the Director of National Intelligence (DNI) in case of the DNI's death, resignation, or inability to perform their duties. The designated officers are listed in order of succession, and the memorandum also outlines exceptions and limitations to the order of succession. It revokes a previous presidential memorandum from 2011 and states that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits. The memorandum is directed to be published in the Federal Register.